                <div id="title">
                    <h1>USN-2305-1: Samba vulnerability</h1>
                </div>

                <div id="content" class="clearfix content-area">

    
<h2>Ubuntu Security Notice USN-2305-1</h2>
<p><em>1st August, 2014</em></p>
<h3>samba vulnerability</h3>
<p>A security issue affects these releases of Ubuntu and its 
    derivatives:</p>
<ul>

    <li>Ubuntu 14.04 LTS</li>

</ul>


<h3>Summary</h3>
<p>Samba could be made to run programs as an administrator if it received
specially crafted network traffic.
</p>



<h3>Software description</h3>
<ul>

  
    <li>samba 
    - SMB/CIFS file, print, and login server for Unix
    
    </li>
  

</ul>


<h3>Details</h3>
<p>Volker Lendecke discovered that the Samba NetBIOS name service daemon<br />incorrectly handled certain memory operations. A remote attacker could use<br />this issue to execute arbitrary code as the root user.<br /></p>

<h3>Update instructions</h3>
<p> The problem can be corrected by updating your system to the following
package version:</p>
<dl>

<dt>Ubuntu 14.04 LTS:</dt>
  
    
  <dd>
    <a href="https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/samba">samba</a>
    <span>
        <a href="https://launchpad.net/ubuntu/+source/samba/2:4.1.6+dfsg-1ubuntu2.14.04.3">2:4.1.6+dfsg-1ubuntu2.14.04.3</a>
    </span>
  </dd>
    
  

</dl>
<p>To update your system, please follow these instructions:
<a href="https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Security/Upgrades">https://wiki.ubuntu.com/Security/Upgrades</a>.
</p>
<p>In general, a standard system update will make all the necessary changes.<br /></p>



<h3>References</h3>
<p>

        <a href="http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/CVE-2014-3560">CVE-2014-3560</a>
        

</p>





